<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The assignment mono_clock_source = _MHD_CLOCK_GETTIME; sets a local variable that is never used to affect program state in the compiled configuration. In the shown function a local enum _MHD_mono_clock_source mono_clock_source is declared and only later either (a) is tested in a #ifdef HAVE_CLOCK_GET_TIME block (which is not defined in the provided configuration) or (b) is cast to void to suppress a warning. Because HAVE_CLOCK_GET_TIME is not defined, the variable’s value is not used to change program behaviour and the assignment has no observable effect (it only affects the local shadowed variable). Therefore the operation is dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
